==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sincerely
<hw>Sin*cere"ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>In a sincere manner.</def>
Specifically: <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Purely; without alloy.</def>
<au>Milton.</au> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Honestly; unfeignedly; without
dissimulation; <as>as, to speak one's mind <ex>sincerely</ex>; to love
virtue <ex>sincerely</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sincereness</ent>⟦br⟧
